crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a highly comprehensive Information Stealer (Infostealer) that systematically targets a wide range of sensitive user data for exfiltration. Upon execution, it establishes a network connection to a C2 server at 172.28.212.224:3131. It utilizes process injection by launching a headless instance of Google Chrome and using CreateRemoteThread/WriteProcessMemory to execute received code. The malware's primary functionality includes harvesting credentials, session tokens, and databases from web browsers (Chrome, Edge, Opera, Vivaldi), communication platforms (Discord, Telegram, Signal, WhatsApp, Slack, Teams, Skype), and gaming services (Steam). Additionally, it targets cryptocurrency wallets (MetaMask, Exodus, Atomic, Trust Wallet), VPN configurations, FTP clients, and email clients (Outlook, Foxmail). It also performs system reconnaissance, captures screenshots, monitors the clipboard, and extracts Wi-Fi passwords using 'netsh'. All collected data is sent back to the C2 via the established socket.
